               <p>PETER DUFF. I am a <rs id="t18230514-37-viclabel203" type="occupation">linendraper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230514-37-victim398 t18230514-37-viclabel203"></join>, and live in Brewer-street. In the afternoon of the 1st of February, I gave the prisoner two pieces of linen, measuring fifty-three yards, to carry into the City - he was a <rs id="t18230514-37-deflabel204" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230514-37-defend396 t18230514-37-deflabel204"></join>, but not in my employ; he never returned to be paid. His brother called on me next day. I saw the linen at Marlborough-street, last week. I gave him no authority to pawn it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230514-37-person399">
